<paragraph id="8B823C6AFFF5F5240CE9DF61FE6CFC89" blockId="24.[168,466,783,808]" box="[168,466,783,808]" pageId="24" pageNumber="531">
<heading id="D0CA8B06FFF5F5240CE9DF61FE6CFC89" box="[168,466,783,808]" fontSize="10" level="2" pageId="24" pageNumber="531" reason="2">
<taxonomicName id="4C3D47E9FFF5F5240CE9DF61FE6CFC89" authority="Nees" box="[168,466,783,808]" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Eragrostis" kingdom="Plantae" order="Poales" pageId="24" pageNumber="531" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="polytricha">
<emphasis id="B949E078FFF5F5240CE9DF61FE6CFC89" bold="true" box="[168,466,783,808]" inLineHeading="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="531" reason="1">
<emphasis id="B949E078FFF5F5240CE9DF61FE2BFC86" bold="true" box="[168,405,783,808]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="531">Eragrostis polytricha</emphasis>
Nees
</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B823C6AFFF5F5240CE9DF47FE7CFC56" blockId="24.[166,779,822,1506]" pageId="24" pageNumber="531">
<emphasis id="B949E078FFF5F5240CE9DF47FEF4FCEF" bold="true" box="[168,330,822,846]" pageId="24" pageNumber="531">Identification.</emphasis>
Perennial tussock grass, 
<quantity id="4CC5918FFFF5F5240E15DF46FD05FCEF" box="[596,699,823,847]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.75" metricValueMax="7.5" metricValueMin="2.0" pageId="24" pageNumber="531" unit="cm" value="47.5" valueMax="75.0" valueMin="20.0">20–75 cm</quantity>
height. Leaf-blades linear, without glandules, trichomes densely present on both sides, 
<quantity id="4CC5918FFFF5F5240DDDDF0BFE45FC30" box="[412,507,890,914]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.85" metricValueMax="2.8" metricValueMin="0.9" pageId="24" pageNumber="531" unit="cm" value="18.5" valueMax="28.0" valueMin="9.0">9–28 cm</quantity>
long, 
<quantity id="4CC5918FFFF5F5240E01DF0BFD79FC30" box="[576,711,890,914]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.65" metricValueMax="5.0" metricValueMin="2.3" pageId="24" pageNumber="531" unit="cm" value="0.365" valueMax="0.5" valueMin="0.23">0.23–0.5 cm</quantity>
wide, ligulate. It is identified by its open panicle, 
<quantity id="4CC5918FFFF5F5240EDCDFEAFCB5FC12" box="[669,779,923,947]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.2" metricValueMax="2.9" metricValueMin="1.5" pageId="24" pageNumber="531" unit="cm" value="22.0" valueMax="29.0" valueMin="15.0">15–29 cm</quantity>
long, 
<quantity id="4CC5918FFFF5F5240CA6DFCCFEEDFC74" box="[231,339,957,981]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.85" metricValueMax="2.3" metricValueMin="1.4" pageId="24" pageNumber="531" unit="cm" value="18.5" valueMax="23.0" valueMin="14.0">14–23 cm</quantity>
wide, with trichomes present along the main axis and at the axils.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C3276FE1FFF5F5240CE9D874FE40FBBC" box="[168,510,1029,1054]" pageId="24" pageNumber="531" type="description">
<paragraph id="8B823C6AFFF5F5240CE9D874FE40FBBC" blockId="24.[166,779,822,1506]" box="[168,510,1029,1054]" pageId="24" pageNumber="531">
<emphasis id="B949E078FFF5F5240CE9D874FEE3FBBF" bold="true" box="[168,349,1029,1054]" pageId="24" pageNumber="531">Common name.</emphasis>
Palha-voadora
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C3276FE1FFF5F5240CE9D85DFEFEFB0F" pageId="24" pageNumber="531" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8B823C6AFFF5F5240CE9D85DFD57FBE5" blockId="24.[166,779,822,1506]" box="[168,745,1068,1093]" pageId="24" pageNumber="531">
<emphasis id="B949E078FFF5F5240CE9D85DFEA9FBE5" bold="true" box="[168,279,1068,1092]" pageId="24" pageNumber="531">Remarks.</emphasis>
A common species at the native grassland.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B823C6AFFF5F5240CE9D822FEFEFB0F" blockId="24.[166,779,822,1506]" pageId="24" pageNumber="531">
<emphasis id="B949E078FFF5F5240CE9D822FEDBFBCA" bold="true" box="[168,357,1107,1131]" pageId="24" pageNumber="531">Brazilian range.</emphasis>
Midwest, North (RR state), Northeast (BA, PB and PE states), South and Southeast (except RJ state) regions.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
